  <p>3D printed parts produced by 3D3D are not certified for safety-critical, load-bearing, life-support, or medical applications unless explicitly stated in writing. FDM (Fused Deposition Modeling) parts have inherent layer adhesion limitations and are not equivalent to injection-molded or machined components. The buyer assumes all responsibility for determining fitness for purpose. 3D3D is not liable for injury, damage, or loss resulting from the use of fabricated parts in applications beyond their stated design intent.</p>

  <h2>3. Material Performance</h2>
  <p>Material specifications (temperature resistance, UV stability, chemical resistance, tensile strength) are provided based on manufacturer datasheets and general FDM printing conditions. Actual performance varies based on print orientation, infill density, layer adhesion, post-processing, and environmental exposure. Published material data should be treated as guidance, not guaranteed specifications for your application.</p>

  <h2>4. Travel & Flight Cost Estimates</h2>
  <p>Travel cost estimates displayed on this website are calculated using publicly available statistical fare data and distance-based modeling. They are estimates only and do not represent actual bookable fares. Actual flight costs vary based on booking date, airline, route availability, season, and demand. 3D3D does not operate as a travel agency and makes no guarantee of travel pricing. Final travel costs for on-site deployments are confirmed at the time of booking.</p>

